      "content": "I see. So you're saying the risk is high enough that we just have to regulate regardless of the economic or competitive impact? Some researchers say \"existential risk\" is basically unprovable and just a speculative theory used to drive policy. Is it actually a consensus that these risks are a real possibility, or is it just one specific school of thought?",
